messages.content: 1) The time I felt the biggest sense of relief was also the worst and most depressing moment in my life.  Why?  Because, if it's the worst moment of my life, that means things could only get better, right?
2) Contrary to what everyone thinks, there do exist pictures with me smiling in them.

3) My old username, "Nobody557", came from 8th grade, when I was making a new username and I thought it would be funny if people would refer to me as "Nobody" (the numbers were added in at the end cuz I thought adding numbers to a username was necessary).  My new username "Profound" came to be because I was trying to make a unique, one-word username in osu! and for some reason I remembered it as some random vocabulary word from Mr. Sandknop's 8th grade English class.  Kind of coincidental how both these usernames seemed to stem from 8th grade.

4) I used to love Lego: Ninjago as a kid, and I have several of the series' Lego sets.  My first set was "Cole's Tread Assault" and my final set was the "Temple of Airjitzu".  I probably spent over $500 getting all these sets.

5) From the age of 3-13, I tried writing my own series about a group of five people with elemental powers who ventured the universe and hunted down demons from alternate universes.  5 months ago, I dug up these notebooks, cringed at how bad they were, and paper-shredded 1000+ pages worth of stories.  This concept art is the only thing I have left of it.

6) Every day is an opportunity for you to become a relatively less or more shitty person.  Don't fucking become a relatively shittier person, you stupid dumbfuck, because then you'll have to put even more work to becoming a less shitty person.  Who seriously wants to pile more work on themselves?  What a fucking dumbass.
